attributes.value: / This function performs some trial divisions, then reps Miller-Rabin probabilistic primality tests. A higher reps value will reduce the chances of a non-prime being identified as “probably prime”. A composite number will be identified as a prime with a probability of less than 4^(-reps). Reasonable values of reps are between 15 and 50.
